===pronoun===
'''who''' (singular or plural, nominative case)
''Possessive'': [[whose]].
''Objective case'': [[whom]]. 
(Note that ''who'' is often used instead of ''whom'', especially in informal writing or conversation.)

#what person or people; which person or people. (used in a direct or indirect question)
#:''Who is that?'' (direct question)
#:''I don't know who it is.'' (indirect question)
#the person or people that (used as a [[relative pronoun]])
#:''It was a nice man who helped us.''


